Root Directory:

/
 package.json
 app.js <----- This should drive/start the austin-tv backend as well as the web frontend
                The web frontend may just be marked "available" through nginx (like a mv .file file)
 atv-modules/
             *Core modules will live here*
             ffmpeg-handler
             ffmpeg-distributor <-- implementing is a stretch goal, to push across multiple ec2 instances for encoding
             web-middleware <---- Web interface, web middleware(API endpoints), database stuff
             atv-middleware/  <---this is where the plugins live
                            atv-plugin-youtube/ <--- the reference youtube plugin
                                                     receives a youtube link from web interface(listens on plugin 'daemon')
                                                     calls youtube-dl, gets resulting .mp4 file, and then asks ffmpeg-handler
                                                     to begin an rtmp stream for <user_id> that replaces the running one in-line (nginx)
             plugin-daemon.js <- would this be better as just the app.js and then launch *everything* as an atv plugin?
/

